                          <h2>Introduction to Agenda</h2>
                          <div class="divide20"></div>
                          <h3>Agenda: Annexation of Czechoslovakia, 1939</h3>
                          <p>Relations across Europe are souring, and the fear of War is on constant rise. In such a scenario, the primary objective of this Council will be to examine the legitimacy and efficacy of the Munich Pact and further deliberate over the Annexation of Czechoslovakia in 1939. However, the greater objective will be the prevention of War and continuation of peaceful co-existence. Thus, this Council would be expected to discuss the armament race across nations, the need or harms of colonisation and provisions that need to be made to ensure greater lasting peace and mutual co-operation. At this point it is necessary not to view the Agenda in a vacuum, apart from the actions by Nazi Germany in Europe tensions are rising in Asia. Japanese aggression in China has been taking place since the early 1930s; this council must also work towards an effective resolution of this crisis as well.</p>
                          <p>This committee has been tasked with a difficult mandate, but times of moral crisis require extraordinary efforts. The task of preventing war, genocide and destruction rests in your hands. Ultimately, allow your conscience to guide you in your deliberations and discussions and remain true to your nation.</p>

